{
  "doc_id": "35004",
  "text": "Recently, two 3D-FDG parameters of metabolic tumor volume (MTV) and total lesion glycolysis (TLG) have been proposed as the imaging biomarkers of potential interest for diagnostic and prognostic assessment of cancer patients [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . MTV signifies the volume of the tumor tissue, demonstrating increased FDG uptake above a certain threshold. TLG is obtained by multiplying the MTV by the mean SUV.",
